HOLIDAY  TRAFFIC Avoid traffic delays and catch the train to the airport - MASCOT Sydney Airport
properties.publicTransport: Visit transportnswto plan your trip to the airport
properties.otherAdvice:
Travellers heading off on holiday or to visit family or friends this summer are being urged to use public transport as Sydney Airport prepares for the busy holiday period. Large numbers of passengers are expected to fly in and out of Sydney during the school and summer holidays.

Traffic is expected to be heavy on roads in and around the airport with the busiest times between 6am and 11:30am every day at both the T1 International and T2 T3 Domestic terminals, and from 6pm to 10pm at the Domestic terminals.

The T8 Airport and South train line will cater for the increased holiday demand, helping those heading off interstate and overseas as well those arriving into Sydney.

Travellers should strongly consider catching the train, and if they must drive are reminded to allow plenty of additional time and be aware of ongoing work to upgrade roads around the airport precinct, including along Joyce Dr.
properties.displayName: HOLIDAY  TRAFFIC Avoid traffic delays and catch the train to the airport

properties.headline: HOLIDAY PARKING - ROYAL NATIONAL PARK Sir Bertram Stevens Drive
properties.otherAdvice:
The Royal National Park is traditionally busy over the New Year holiday period. As precincts and car parks become full at Wattamolla Beach, Garie Beach, Audley, Maianbar and Bundeena, road closures will be implemented.

When parking capacity is reached across all precincts, traffic will only be permitted to travel through the park. If there are significant delays, both the northern and southern entries to the park via Farnell Ave, Loftus and via Lady Wakehurst Dr, Otford will close.

Entry will be maintained via McKell Ave, Waterfall for residents only. 

Visitors are encouraged to check the Royal National Park local alerts before travelling for updates on precinct access.

Road closures when precincts reach capacity:

- Wattamolla Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Wattamolla Beach
- Garie Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Garie Beach
- Maianbar Rd between Bundeena Dr and Maianbar township
- Bundeena Dr between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Bundeena township.

Traffic controllers and NSW Police will be on-site managing access for local residents on Maianbar Rd and Bundeena Dr upon proof of residential address.

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Controls - NSW-QUEENSLAND Border crossings
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland Government has implemented enhanced border control measures, including border passes and identification screening.

Any person that has been in a declared COVID-19 hotspot during the past 14 days must not enter Queensland. From 1am Thursday 1 October, the NSW border zone has been extended; see the Queensland government website for more information.

Anyone attempting to enter Queensland from NSW must complete a Queensland Border Declaration Pass.

properties.otherAdvice:

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Control - COBAKI LAKES M1 Pacific Motorway at Queensland border
properties.otherAdvice:
A reduced speed limit is implemented in the Tugun Tunnel due to the heavy traffic.

The Queensland Government has implemented enhanced border control measures, including border passes and identification screening.

Any person that has been in a declared COVID-19 hotspot during the past 14 days must not enter Queensland. All of Victoria and Greater Sydney are currently declared COVID-19 hotspots. From 1am Saturday 8 August, all local government areas in NSW and ACT will also be declared COVID-19 hotspots.

Anyone attempting to enter Queensland from NSW at this 24/7 checkpoint must hold a valid Queensland Border Declaration Pass.

Pass holders should allow plenty of additional travel time to cross the NSW-Queensland border, particularly during peak periods.
